\n1. according to preliminary .figure*, J.\nCheever Cowdln, chairman of the\nboard, announced today. The final\nfigure* will be available by the end\nof January.\nThl* is the first time that the com\npany has been \"In the black\" since\nthe quarter ended November 2, 1*35.\nRestoration of profitable operations\nIs the result of a comprehensive pro\ngram of reorganizing the company's\nset-up. policies and personnel Inaugu\nrated by the new Interests who as\nsumed control of the company In\nApril, 1B3(, according to Mr. Cowdln.\nBookings for the current quarter\nare running 50 per cent ahead of last\nyear. The company's new musical\npicture, \"You're a Sweetheart,\u201d star\nring Alice Faye, which has Just opened\nin New York, promises to be profitable,\nas it already has produced 250 day\nand-date bookings, a new record for\nthe company.\nEXTENSION IS GRANTED\nFOR UTILITIES POWER\nBy tie Associated Tress.\nCHICAGO, Dec. 27.\u2014Federal Judge\nWilliam H. Holly today extended un\ntil January 20 the time for filing ad\nditional. reorganization plans for the\nUtilities Power A Light Corp.\nAtlas Corp., holder of a major in\nterest in Utilities Power A Light, has\nfiled the only plan to date.\nFiling objections was set for Feb\nruary 3 and arguments for February\n14.\nRAILWAY INCOME.\nNEW YORK Dec. 27 >p .\u2014Net ODeratini\nincome \u2018before fixed charge* and other\nincome* of railroads reporting today for\nNovember included.\n1927. 1928.\nBaltimore A Ohio $898,207 $0,988,701\nBurlington 1.290.700 1.585.528\nChicago East n 111 180.845 045.180\nChicago Nor western 188.882 1.105.704\nNorthern Pacific 7 50.894 1.819 174\nPitts. 4t\u00abLake Erie 181.089 518.185\nSanta Pe 3 150 858 2 897.229\nAtlantic Coast 904.049 502.845\nBoston A Maine _ J 7 9.27 4 894 215\nCentral New Jersey 80.881 108.009\nChgo Rock Island 097.954 500.918\nDela Hudson 185 890 417.898\nDela Lack _ 284.905 804 490\nDenver Rio Gr_ 108.804 988 505\nLehigh Valley 07 1.401 844.582\nLouisville Nash_ 1.01 